    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I really think it is a BUG actually. You are absolutely right there should be configurable limit for number of threads. But code needs to be fixed to not spawn so many threads at first.\r\n\r\nI ran into this issue as well after grpc upgrade from 1.1.4 (no additional grpc_executor threads) to 1.12.0 (112 dummy threads on my 56-core box).\r\n\r\nAs I can understand it is something related to the usage of grpc_executor_scheduler(GRPC_EXECUTOR_LONG) in the TCP code (see cover_self)."
